💾 Amazon S3 Storage Classes
 1️⃣ S3 Standard
Designed for frequently accessed data.
- Low latency
- High throughput
- 99.99% availability
- 11 nines durability
Use Cases:-
- Websites
- Mobile Applications
- Frequently accessed files

2️⃣ S3 Intelligent-Tiering
Automatically moves data between storage tiers depending on how frequently it is accessed.This helps reduce storage costs without impacting application performance.
Best For:-
- Unknown access patterns
- Long-term storage
- Cost optimization

3️⃣ S3 Standard-Infrequent Access (Standard-IA)
Designed for data that is accessed less frequently but must be retrieved quickly whenever needed.
Provides lower storage costs while maintaining high durability.
Best For:-
- Backups
- Disaster Recovery
- Long-term storage

4️⃣ S3 One Zone-Infrequent Access (One Zone-IA)
Stores data in a single Availability Zone, making it less expensive than Standard-IA.
Suitable for data that can be recreated if needed.
Best For:-
- Secondary backups
- Temporary files
- Re-creatable data

5️⃣ S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval
Provides low-cost archival storage while allowing data retrieval within milliseconds.
Ideal for archived data that still requires immediate access.
Best For:-
- Medical Records
- Image Archives
- Media Libraries

6️⃣ S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval
Offers very low-cost archival storage for data that is rarely accessed.
Retrieval time ranges from 1 minute to 12 hours.
Best For:-
- Compliance archives
- Backup storage
- Long-term business records

7️⃣ S3 Glacier Deep Archive
The lowest-cost Amazon S3 storage class.
Retrieval can take up to 12 hours, making it suitable for data that is rarely accessed.
Best For:-
- Legal Documents
- Financial Records
- Regulatory Compliance
- Long-term Archival

🔄 Versioning
Versioning allows Amazon S3 to keep multiple versions of an object.
Benefits:
- Recover deleted files
- Restore previous versions
- Prevent accidental overwrites

Example:
    resume.pdf (v1)
        ↓
    resume.pdf (v2)
        ↓
    resume.pdf (v3)

🔐 Security
Amazon S3 provides multiple layers of security.
- IAM Policies
- Bucket Policies
- Block Public Access
- Encryption at Rest
- Encryption in Transit
- Versioning
- MFA Delete
Encryption options include:
- SSE-S3
- SSE-KMS
- SSE-C

♻️ Lifecycle Policies
Lifecycle Policies automatically move data to lower-cost storage classes or delete old objects.
Example:
        S3 Standard
           ↓
        30 Days
           ↓
        Standard-IA
           ↓
        90 Days
           ↓
        Glacier
           ↓
        Delete
This helps reduce storage costs automatically.

🌎 Cross Region Replication (CRR)
Cross Region Replication automatically copies objects from one AWS Region to another.
Benefits:
- Disaster Recovery
- High Availability
- Compliance Requirements

🌐 Static Website Hosting
Amazon S3 can host static websites.
Supported files include:
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- Images

Perfect for:
- Portfolio Websites
- Landing Pages
- Documentation Sites

📢 Event Notifications
Amazon S3 can trigger AWS services whenever an event occurs.
Examples:
- AWS Lambda
- Amazon SNS
- Amazon SQS
Example:
    File Uploaded
        ↓
    Amazon S3
        ↓
    AWS Lambda
        ↓
  Resize Image

💰 Why Amazon S3?
Amazon S3 helps organizations:
- Store unlimited data
- Reduce storage costs
- Improve security
- Automatically scale
- Protect data with 11 nines durability
- Simplify backup and disaster recovery
Instead of managing storage infrastructure, developers can focus on building applications while AWS securely stores and manages their data.

